Kali Live Boot:
If you make a Kali Live Boot USB you can bypass login and access the Hard Drive of devices which don't have Hard Drive encryption
Restart to boot menu (F12, F10, F2, whichever one it is) and choose to boot from Kali USB
When it boots, you can see the Hard Drive in the tree on the left if you open a file manager
Save files to another USB or partition the Kali Live USB to have extra space for saving files

Linux:
Restart linux to GRUB boot menu
Press e
look for line that starts with "Linux"
Replace end of line starting with "init" with "init re /bin/bash"
Reboot
You will reboot to a root shell

